      "description": "Counts scheduler loops where DiskBalancer is still running but did not queue any container move. 'No Suitable Volume/Container' increments when the policy cannot find a valid source/destination volume pair with a movable container (for example, disks are already even, density is below threshold, or no container matches the allowed states). 'Throttled' increments when the scheduler deliberately waits because the configured bandwidth limit was reached.",
